mary baine campbell republics of letters a journal for the study of knowledge politics and the arts link to arcade home editors blog issues rss contact admin login home mary baine campbell mary baine campbell is a poet and professor of english at brandeis university she has published extensively on early modern literature and culture poetry travel writing and the history of science her current research interests include the early modern history of dreams and dream theory in light of developments in both representation including poetry and natural philosophy or science and utopia past and present fora between experience and experiment limits of the atlantic republican tradition on sovereignty rethinking the republic of letters the leland stanford jr university seal issn 2159 1873
